name: Pre-spatial Component #1
description: "The pre-spatial field is a place without a name": "where infinity and existence merge in a long and inconceivable sea." "Surely that's where dreams or lost pets live": "wandering around in an eternal, black torpor, so full and so empty." "Things even have no form": "their forces and tensions impact our experiences." "Nameless night, turn your light out of the way." }  Pre Spatial Component # 1  The pre-spatial field is a layer adjacent to all devices where the data has no qualities. They behave like a haze or storm of data relationships.
